 100    Qt_Annotator_Window is a GUI class for annotating PD curves.

 102    The annotator works with PD curves and allows
 103    selection of a single points (labelled as pdOnset in the saved file).
 104    The GUI also displays the waveform, and if TextGrids
 105    are provided, the acoustic segment boundaries.

 321    def change_to_dark(self):
 322        """Activate dark mode."""
 323        mpl_style(dark=True)
 324
 325    def change_to_light(self):
 326        """Activate light mode."""
 327        mpl_style(dark=False)

 329    @property
 330    def current(self):
 331        """Current recording index."""
 332        return self.recordings[self.index]
 333
 334    @property
 335    def default_annotations(self):
 336        """List default annotations and their default values as a dict."""
 337        return {
 338            'pdCategory': self.categories[-1],
 339            'tonguePosition': self.tongue_positions[-1],
 340            'selected_time': -1.0,
 341            'selection_index': -1,
 342        }
 343
 344    def _add_annotations(self):
 345        """Add the annotations."""
 346        for recording in self.recordings:
 347            if recording.annotations:
 348                recording.annotations = dict(
 349                    list(self.default_annotations.items()) +
 350                    list(recording.annotations.items()))
 351            else:
 352                recording.annotations = deepcopy(self.default_annotations)
 353
 354    def _get_title(self):
 355        """
 356        Private helper function for generating the title.
 357        """
 358        text = 'Recording: ' + str(self.index + 1) + '/' + str(self.max_index)
 359        text += ', prompt: ' + self.current.metadata.prompt
 360        return text
 361
 362    def _get_long_title(self):
 363        """
 364        Private helper function for generating a longer title for a figure.
 365        """
 366        text = 'Recording: ' + str(self.index + 1) + '/' + str(self.max_index)
 367        text += ', Speaker: ' + str(self.current.metadata.participant_id)
 368        text += ', prompt: ' + self.current.metadata.prompt
 369        return text
 370
 371    def _release_modality_memory(self):
 372        # TODO 1.0: make it possible to select which modalities get their
 373        # memory released
 374        if 'RawUltrasound' in self.current.modalities:
 375            self.current.modalities['RawUltrasound'].data = None
 376
 377    def clear_axes(self):
 378        """Clear data axes of this annotator."""
 379        for axes in self.data_axes:
 380            axes.cla()
 381
 382    def update(self):
 383        """
 384        Updates the graphs but not the buttons.
 385        """
 386        self.clear_axes()
 387        self.draw_plots()
 388        self.multicursor = MultiCursor(
 389            self.canvas,
 390            axes=self.data_axes + self.tier_axes,
 391            color='deepskyblue', linestyle="--", lw=1)
 392        self.figure.canvas.draw()
 393
 394        if self.display_tongue:
 395            _logger.debug("Drawing ultra frame in update")
 396            self.draw_ultra_frame()
 397
 398    def update_ui(self):
 399        """
 400        Updates parts of the UI outwith the graphs.
 401        """
 402        position_annotation = self.current.annotations['tonguePosition']
 403        if position_annotation in self.position_rbs:
 404            button_to_activate = self.position_rbs[position_annotation]
 405            button_to_activate.setChecked(True)
 406
 407        self.goLineEdit.setText(str(self.index + 1))

 409    def plot_modality_axes(
 410            self,
 411            axes_number: int,
 412            axes_name: str,
 413            zero_offset: float = 0,
 414            ylim: list[float, float] | None = None
 415    ) -> None:
 416        """
 417        Plot modalities on a data_axes.
 418
 419        Parameters
 420        ----------
 421        axes_number : int
 422            Which axes, counting from top.
 423        axes_name : str
 424            What should the axes be called. This will be the y_label.
 425        zero_offset : Optional[float], optional
 426            Where do we set 0 in time in relation to the audio, by default 0
 427        ylim : Optional[list[float, float]], optional
 428            y limits, by default None
 429        """
 430        axes_params = self.gui_config.data_axes[axes_name]
 431        data_axes_params = self.gui_config.general_axes_params.data_axes
 432        plot_modality_names = axes_params.modalities
 433
 434        if ylim is None:
 435            if data_axes_params is None and axes_params is None:
 436                ylim = (-0.05, 1.05)
 437            elif data_axes_params.ylim is None and axes_params.ylim is None:
 438                if not data_axes_params.auto_ylim and not axes_params.auto_ylim:
 439                    ylim = (-0.05, 1.05)
 440                else:
 441                    ylim = None
 442            elif axes_params.ylim is None:
 443                ylim = data_axes_params.ylim
 444            else:
 445                ylim = axes_params.ylim
 446
 447        y_offset = 0
 448        if axes_params.y_offset is not None:
 449            y_offset = axes_params.y_offset
 450            ylim_adjustment = y_offset * len(plot_modality_names)
 451            if y_offset > 0:
 452                ylim = (ylim[0], ylim[1] + ylim_adjustment)
 453            else:
 454                ylim = (ylim[0] + ylim_adjustment, ylim[1])
 455
 456        if axes_params.colors_in_sequence:
 457            colors = get_colors_in_sequence(len(plot_modality_names))
 458        else:
 459            colors = None
 460        for i, name in enumerate(plot_modality_names):
 461            modality = self.current.modalities[name]
 462            plot_timeseries(
 463                self.data_axes[axes_number],
 464                modality.data,
 465                modality.timevector - zero_offset,
 466                self.xlim,
 467                ylim=ylim,
 468                color=colors[i],
 469                linestyle=(0, (i + 1, i + 1)),
 470                normalise=axes_params.normalisation,
 471                y_offset=i * y_offset,
 472                label=format_legend(
 473                    modality=modality,
 474                    index=i,
 475                    format_strings=axes_params.modality_names
 476                )
 477            )
 478            if axes_params.mark_peaks:
 479                mark_peaks(self.data_axes[axes_number],
 480                           modality,
 481                           self.xlim,
 482                           display_prominence_values=True,
 483                           time_offset=zero_offset)
 484            self.data_axes[axes_number].set_ylabel(axes_name)
 485
 486        if axes_params.legend:
 487            self.data_axes[axes_number].legend(
 488                loc='upper left',
 489            )
 490
 491    def display_exclusion(self):
 492        """
 493        Updates title and graphs to show this Recording is excluded.
 494        """
 495        self.data_axes[0].set_title(
 496            self._get_title() + "\nNOTE: This recording has been excluded.")
 497
 498    def draw_plots(self):
 499        """
 500        Updates title and graphs. Called by self.update().
 501        """
 502        if self.current.excluded:
 503            self.display_exclusion()
 504
 505        if 'MonoAudio' in self.current.modalities:
 506            self.data_axes[0].set_title(self._get_long_title())
 507        else:
 508            self.data_axes[0].set_title(
 509                self._get_long_title() + "\nNOTE: Audio missing.")
 510            return
 511
 512        for axes in self.tier_axes:
 513            axes.remove()
 514        self.tier_axes = []
 515        if self.current.satgrid:
 516            nro_tiers = len(self.current.satgrid)
 517            self.tier_grid_spec = self.main_grid_spec[1].subgridspec(
 518                nro_tiers, 1, hspace=0, wspace=0)
 519            for axes_counter, tier in enumerate(self.current.textgrid):
 520                axes = self.figure.add_subplot(
 521                    self.tier_grid_spec[axes_counter],
 522                    sharex=self.data_axes[0])
 523                axes.set_yticks([])
 524                self.tier_axes.append(axes)
 525
 526        for axes in self.data_axes:
 527            axes.xaxis.set_tick_params(bottom=False, labelbottom=False)
 528
 529        for axes in self.tier_axes[:-1]:
 530            axes.xaxis.set_tick_params(bottom=False, labelbottom=False)
 531
 532        if 'MonoAudio' not in self.current.modalities:
 533            return
 534
 535        audio = self.current.modalities['MonoAudio']
 536        if audio.go_signal is None:
 537            stimulus_onset = 0
 538        else:
 539            stimulus_onset = audio.go_signal
 540
 541        wav = audio.data
 542        wav_time = audio.timevector - stimulus_onset
 543
 544        self.xlim = (-.25, 1.5)
 545        if self.gui_config.xlim is not None:
 546            self.xlim = self.gui_config.xlim
 547        elif self.gui_config.auto_xlim:
 548            x_minimums = []
 549            x_maximums = []
 550            modalities_to_check = self.gui_config.plotted_modality_names()
 551            modalities_to_check.add("MonoAudio")
 552            for name in modalities_to_check:
 553                if name in self.current:
 554                    x_minimums.append(
 555                        self.current[name].timevector[0] - stimulus_onset)
 556                    x_maximums.append(
 557                        self.current[name].timevector[-1] - stimulus_onset)
 558            self.xlim = (np.min(x_minimums)-.05, np.max(x_maximums)+.05)
 559
 560        axes_counter = 0
 561        for axes_name in self.gui_config.data_axes:
 562            match axes_name:
 563                case "spectrogram":
 564                    if self.gui_config.data_axes[axes_name].ylim is not None:
 565                        ylim = self.gui_config.data_axes[axes_name].ylim
 566                    else:
 567                        ylim = (0, 10500)
 568                    plot_spectrogram(self.data_axes[axes_counter],
 569                                     waveform=wav,
 570                                     ylim=ylim,
 571                                     sampling_frequency=audio.sampling_rate,
 572                                     extent_on_x=(wav_time[0], wav_time[-1]))
 573                case "spectrogram2":
 574                    if self.gui_config.data_axes[axes_name].ylim is not None:
 575                        ylim = self.gui_config.data_axes[axes_name].ylim
 576                    else:
 577                        ylim = (0, 10500)
 578                    plot_spectrogram2(
 579                        self.data_axes[axes_counter],
 580                        waveform=wav,
 581                        ylim=ylim,
 582                        sampling_frequency=audio.sampling_rate,
 583                        extent_on_x=(wav_time[0], wav_time[-1]),
 584                        mode=self.gui_config.color_scheme
 585                    )
 586                # TODO: figure out if this should be just completely removed.
 587                # looks like some old experiment.
 588                # add `image =` to spectrogram2 to make this work:
 589                # case "spectrogram distro":
 590                #     spectrum_data = image.get_array().flatten()

 596                case "wav":
 597                    plot_wav(ax=self.data_axes[axes_counter],

 599                             wav_time=wav_time,
 600                             xlim=self.xlim)
 601                case _:

 603                        self.plot_modality_axes(

 605                            axes_name=axes_name,
 606                            zero_offset=stimulus_onset,
 607                            ylim=self.gui_config.data_axes[axes_name].ylim,

 610
 611        # self.data_axes[0].legend(
 612        #     loc='upper left')

 678    def draw_ultra_frame(self):
 679        """
 680        Display an already interpolated ultrasound frame.
 681        """
 682        if self.current.annotations['selection_index'] == -1:
 683            self.action_export_ultrasound_frame.setEnabled(False)
 684            self.ultra_axes.clear()
 685            image_name = 'AggregateImage mean on RawUltrasound'
 686            if image_name in self.current.statistics:
 687                stat = self.current.statistics[image_name]
 688                image = stat.data
 689                self.ultra_axes.imshow(
 690                    image, interpolation='nearest', cmap='gray',
 691                    extent=(-image.shape[1] / 2 - .5, image.shape[1] / 2 + .5,
 692                            -.5, image.shape[0] + .5))
 693        elif self.current.annotations['selection_index'] >= 0:
 694            self.action_export_ultrasound_frame.setEnabled(True)
 695            self.ultra_axes.clear()
 696            index = self.current.annotations['selection_index']
 697
 698            ultrasound = self.current.modalities['RawUltrasound']
 699            image = ultrasound.interpolated_image(index)
 700
 701            self.ultra_axes.imshow(
 702                image, interpolation='nearest', cmap='gray',
 703                extent=(-image.shape[1] / 2 - .5, image.shape[1] / 2 + .5,
 704                        -.5, image.shape[0] + .5))
 705
 706            if 'Splines' in self.current.modalities:
 707                splines = self.current.modalities['Splines']
 708                index = self.current.annotations['selection_index']
 709                ultra = self.current.modalities['RawUltrasound']
 710                timestamp = ultra.timevector[index]
 711
 712                spline_index = np.argmin(
 713                    np.abs(splines.timevector - timestamp))
 714
 715                # TODO: move this to reading splines/end of loading and make
 716                # the system warn the user when there is a creeping
 717                # discrepancy. also make it an integration test where
 718                # spline_test_token1 gets run and triggers this
 719                # ic(splines.timevector)
 720                # ic(ultra.timevector[:len(splines.timevector)])
 721                # time_diff = splines.timevector - \
 722                #     ultra.timevector[:len(splines.timevector)]
 723                # ic(np.diff(time_diff, n=1))
 724                # ic(np.max(np.abs(np.diff(time_diff, n=1))))
 725
 726                epsilon = max((self.main_config.epsilon, splines.time_precision))
 727                min_difference = abs(
 728                    splines.timevector[spline_index] - timestamp)
 729                # maybe this instead when loading data
 730                # str(number)[::-1].find('.') -> precision
 731
 732                # ic(epsilon, splines.timevector[spline_index] - timestamp)
 733                # ic(splines.timevector[spline_index], timestamp)
 734                if min_difference > epsilon:
 735                    _logger.info("Splines out of synch in %s.",
 736                                 self.current.basename)
 737                    _logger.info("Minimal difference: %f, epsilon: %f",
 738                                 min_difference, epsilon)
 739
 740                spline_config = self.session.metadata.spline_config
 741                if spline_config.data_config:
 742                    limits = spline_config.data_config.ignore_points
 743                    plot_spline(self.ultra_axes,
 744                                splines.cartesian_spline(spline_index),
 745                                limits=limits)
 746                else:
 747                    plot_spline(self.ultra_axes,
 748                                splines.cartesian_spline(spline_index))
 749            else:
 750                _logger.info("No splines")
 751        self.ultra_canvas.draw()

 753    def draw_raw_ultra_frame(self):
 754        """
 755        Interpolate and display a raw ultrasound frame.
 756        """
 757        if self.current.annotations['selection_index'] > -1:
 758            self.action_export_ultrasound_frame.setEnabled(True)
 759            ind = self.current.annotations['selection_index']
 760            array = self.current.modalities['RawUltrasound'].data[ind, :, :]
 761        else:
 762            self.action_export_ultrasound_frame.setEnabled(False)
 763            if self.current.statistics['Aggregate mean on RawUltrasound']:
 764                array = self.current.modalities[
 765                    'Aggregate mean on RawUltrasound'].data
 766            else:
 767                array = self.current.modalities['RawUltrasound'].data[1, :, :]
 768        array = np.transpose(array)
 769        array = np.flip(array, 0).copy()
 770        array = array.astype(np.int8)
 771        self.ultra_axes.imshow(array, interpolation='nearest', cmap='gray')
 772        self.ultra_canvas.draw()

 774    def next(self):
 775        """
 776        Callback function for the Next button.
 777        Increases cursor index, updates the view.
 778        """

 782            self.update()

 785    def _update_pd_onset(self):
 786        audio = self.current.modalities['MonoAudio']
 787        if audio.go_signal is None:
 788            stimulus_onset = 0
 789        else:
 790            stimulus_onset = audio.go_signal
 791
 792        if 'PD l1 on RawUltrasound' in self.current.modalities:
 793            pd_metrics = self.current.modalities['PD l1 on RawUltrasound']
 794            ultra_time = pd_metrics.timevector - stimulus_onset
 795            index = self.current.annotations['selection_index']
 796            self.current.annotations['selected_time'] = ultra_time[index]

 798    def next_frame(self):
 799        """
 800        Move the data cursor to the next frame.
 801        """
 802        if 'PD l1 on RawUltrasound' not in self.current.modalities:
 803            return
 804
 805        selection_index = self.current.annotations['selection_index']
 806        pd = self.current.modalities['PD l1 on RawUltrasound']
 807        data_length = pd.data.size
 808        if -1 < selection_index < data_length:
 809            self.current.annotations['selection_index'] += 1
 810            _logger.debug(
 811                "next frame: %d",
 812                (self.current.annotations['selection_index']))
 813            self._update_pd_onset()
 814            self.update()
 815            self.update_ui()
 816
 817    def previous_frame(self):
 818        """
 819        Move the data cursor to the previous frame.
 820        """
 821        if self.current.annotations['selection_index'] > 0:
 822            self.current.annotations['selection_index'] -= 1
 823            _logger.debug(
 824                "previous frame: %d",
 825                (self.current.annotations['selection_index']))
 826            self._update_pd_onset()
 827            self.update()
 828            self.update_ui()

1068    def export_annotations_and_metadata(self) -> None:
1069        """
1070        Export annotations and some other meta data.
1071        """
1072        (filename, _) = QFileDialog.getSaveFileName(
1073            self, 'Save file', directory='.', filter="CSV files (*.csv)")
1074
1075        if not filename:
1076            return
1077
1078        vowels = ['a', 'A', 'e', 'E', 'i', 'I',
1079                  'o', 'O', 'u', '@', "@`", 'OI', 'V']
1080        fieldnames = ['basename', 'date_and_time', 'prompt', 'C1', 'C1_dur',
1081                      'word_dur', 'first_sound',
1082                      'first_sound_type', 'first_sound_dur', 'AAI']
1083        fieldnames.extend(self.default_annotations.keys())
1084        csv.register_dialect('tabseparated', delimiter='\t',
1085                             quoting=csv.QUOTE_NONE)
1086
1087        with closing(open(filename, 'w', encoding='utf-8')) as csvfile:
1088            writer = csv.DictWriter(csvfile, fieldnames, extrasaction='ignore',
1089                                    dialect='tabseparated')
1090
1091            writer.writeheader()
1092            for recording in self.recordings:
1093                annotations = recording.annotations.copy()
1094                annotations['basename'] = recording.basename
1095                annotations['date_and_time'] = (
1096                    recording.metadata.time_of_recording)
1097                annotations['prompt'] = recording.metadata.prompt
1098                annotations['word'] = recording.metadata.prompt.split()[0]
1099
1100                word_dur = -1.0
1101                acoustic_onset = -1.0
1102                if 'word' in recording.textgrid:
1103                    for interval in recording.textgrid['word']:
1104                        # change this to access the phonemeDict and
1105                        # check for included words, then search for
1106                        # phonemes based on the same
1107                        if interval.text == "":
1108                            continue
1109
1110                        # Before 1.0: check if there is a duration to use here.
1111                        # and maybe make this more intelligent by selecting
1112                        # purposefully the last non-empty first and taking the
1113                        # duration?
1114                        word_dur = interval.dur
1115                        stimulus_onset = (
1116                            recording['MonoAudio'].go_signal)
1117                        acoustic_onset = interval.xmin - stimulus_onset
1118                        break
1119                    annotations['word_dur'] = word_dur
1120                else:
1121                    annotations['word_dur'] = -1.0
1122
1123                if acoustic_onset < 0 or annotations['selected_time'] < 0:
1124                    aai = -1.0
1125                else:
1126                    aai = acoustic_onset - annotations['selected_time']
1127                annotations['AAI'] = aai
1128
1129                first_sound_dur = -1.0
1130                first_sound = ""
1131                if 'segment' in recording.textgrid:
1132                    for interval in recording.textgrid['segment']:
1133                        if interval.text and interval.text != 'beep':
1134                            first_sound_dur = interval.dur
1135                            first_sound = interval.text
1136                            break
1137                annotations['first_sound_dur'] = first_sound_dur
1138                annotations['first_sound'] = first_sound
1139                if first_sound in vowels:
1140                    annotations['first_sound_type'] = 'V'
1141                else:
1142                    annotations['first_sound_type'] = 'C'
1143
1144                annotations['C1'] = recording.metadata.prompt[0]
1145                writer.writerow(annotations)
1146            _logger.info(
1147                "Wrote onset data in file %s.", filename)

1167    def onpick(self, event):
1168        """
1169        Callback for handling time selection on events.
1170        """
1171        if not event.xdata:
1172            self.current.annotations['selected_time'] = -1
1173            self.current.annotations['selection_index'] = -1
1174            self.update()
1175            return
1176
1177        subplot = 0
1178        for i, axes in enumerate(self.data_axes):
1179            if axes == event.inaxes:
1180                subplot = i + 1
1181                break
1182
1183        _logger.debug(
1184            "Inside onpick - subplot: %d, x=%f",
1185            subplot, event.xdata)
1186
1187        # if subplot == 1:
1188        #     self.current.annotations['selected_time'] = event.pickx
1189
1190        audio = self.current.modalities['MonoAudio']
1191        if audio.go_signal is None:
1192            stimulus_onset = 0
1193        else:
1194            stimulus_onset = audio.go_signal
1195
1196        timevector = (
1197            self.current.modalities['PD l1 on RawUltrasound'].timevector)
1198        distances = np.abs(timevector - stimulus_onset - event.xdata)
1199        self.current.annotations['selection_index'] = np.argmin(distances)
1200        self.current.annotations['selected_time'] = event.xdata
1201
1202        _logger.debug(
1203            "Inside onpick - subplot: %d, index=%d, x=%f",
1204            subplot,
1205            self.current.annotations['selection_index'],
1206            self.current.annotations['selected_time'])
1207
1208        self.update()

1218    def keyPressEvent(self, event):
1219        """
1220        Key press callback.
1221
1222        QtPy is silly and wants the callback to have this specific name.
1223        """
1224        if event.key() == Qt.Key.Key_Shift:
1225            self.shift_is_held = True
1226        if event.key() == Qt.Key.Key_I:
1227            self.gui_config.auto_xlim = False
1228            if self.current.annotations['selection_index'] >= 0:
1229                center = self.current.annotations['selected_time']
1230            else:
1231                center = (self.xlim[0] + self.xlim[1]) / 2.0
1232            length = (self.xlim[1] - self.xlim[0]) * .25
1233            self.xlim = (center - length, center + length)
1234            if self.gui_config.xlim is not None:
1235                self.gui_config.xlim = self.xlim
1236            self.update()
1237        elif event.key() == Qt.Key.Key_O:
1238            self.gui_config.auto_xlim = False
1239            center = (self.xlim[0] + self.xlim[1]) / 2.0
1240            length = self.xlim[1] - self.xlim[0]
1241            self.xlim = (center - length, center + length)
1242            if self.gui_config.xlim is not None:
1243                self.gui_config.xlim = self.xlim
1244            self.update()
1245        elif event.key() == Qt.Key.Key_A:
1246            self.gui_config.auto_xlim = True
1247            self.gui_config.xlim = None
1248            self.update()
1249
1250    # noinspection PyPep8Naming
1251    def keyReleaseEvent(self, event):
1252        """
1253        Key release callback.
1254
1255        QtPy is silly and wants the callback to have this specific name.
1256        """
1257        if event.key() == Qt.Key.Key_Shift:
1258            self.shift_is_held = False

1264        if scheme == Qt.ColorScheme.Light:
1265            self.change_to_light()
1266        else:
1267            self.change_to_dark()

 410    def plot_modality_axes(
 411            self,
 412            axes_number: int,
 413            axes_name: str,
 414            zero_offset: float = 0,
 415            ylim: list[float, float] | None = None
 416    ) -> None:
 417        """
 418        Plot modalities on a data_axes.
 419
 420        Parameters
 421        ----------
 422        axes_number : int
 423            Which axes, counting from top.
 424        axes_name : str
 425            What should the axes be called. This will be the y_label.
 426        zero_offset : Optional[float], optional
 427            Where do we set 0 in time in relation to the audio, by default 0
 428        ylim : Optional[list[float, float]], optional
 429            y limits, by default None
 430        """
 431        axes_params = self.gui_config.data_axes[axes_name]
 432        data_axes_params = self.gui_config.general_axes_params.data_axes
 433        plot_modality_names = axes_params.modalities
 434
 435        if ylim is None:
 436            if data_axes_params is None and axes_params is None:
 437                ylim = (-0.05, 1.05)
 438            elif data_axes_params.ylim is None and axes_params.ylim is None:
 439                if not data_axes_params.auto_ylim and not axes_params.auto_ylim:
 440                    ylim = (-0.05, 1.05)
 441                else:
 442                    ylim = None
 443            elif axes_params.ylim is None:
 444                ylim = data_axes_params.ylim
 445            else:
 446                ylim = axes_params.ylim
 447
 448        y_offset = 0
 449        if axes_params.y_offset is not None:
 450            y_offset = axes_params.y_offset
 451            ylim_adjustment = y_offset * len(plot_modality_names)
 452            if y_offset > 0:
 453                ylim = (ylim[0], ylim[1] + ylim_adjustment)
 454            else:
 455                ylim = (ylim[0] + ylim_adjustment, ylim[1])
 456
 457        if axes_params.colors_in_sequence:
 458            colors = get_colors_in_sequence(len(plot_modality_names))
 459        else:
 460            colors = None
 461        for i, name in enumerate(plot_modality_names):
 462            modality = self.current.modalities[name]
 463            plot_timeseries(
 464                self.data_axes[axes_number],
 465                modality.data,
 466                modality.timevector - zero_offset,
 467                self.xlim,
 468                ylim=ylim,
 469                color=colors[i],
 470                linestyle=(0, (i + 1, i + 1)),
 471                normalise=axes_params.normalisation,
 472                y_offset=i * y_offset,
 473                label=format_legend(
 474                    modality=modality,
 475                    index=i,
 476                    format_strings=axes_params.modality_names
 477                )
 478            )
 479            if axes_params.mark_peaks:
 480                mark_peaks(self.data_axes[axes_number],
 481                           modality,
 482                           self.xlim,
 483                           display_prominence_values=True,
 484                           time_offset=zero_offset)
 485            self.data_axes[axes_number].set_ylabel(axes_name)
 486
 487        if axes_params.legend:
 488            self.data_axes[axes_number].legend(
 489                loc='upper left',
 490            )
 491

 533        if 'MonoAudio' not in self.current.modalities:
 534            return

 537        if audio.go_signal is None:

 571                                     ylim=ylim,
 572                                     sampling_frequency=audio.sampling_rate,
 573                                     extent_on_x=(wav_time[0], wav_time[-1]))
 574                case "spectrogram2":

 589                # add `image =` to spectrogram2 to make this work:

 621        #                  sampling_frequency=l1.sampling_rate,
 622        #                  noverlap=98, NFFT=100,
 623        #                  #  xtent_on_x=[-1, 1])  # ,
 624        #                  xtent_on_x=[ultra_time[0], ultra_time[-1]])  # ,
 625
 626        # segment_line = None
 627        self.animators = []
 628        iterator = zip(self.current.satgrid.items(),
 629                       self.tier_axes, strict=True)
 630        for (name, tier), axis in iterator:
 631            boundaries_by_axis = []
 632
 633            # boundary_set, segment_line = plot_satgrid_tier(
 634            boundary_set, _ = plot_satgrid_tier(
 635                axis, tier, time_offset=stimulus_onset, text_y=.5)
 636            boundaries_by_axis.append(boundary_set)
 637            axis.set_ylabel(
 638                name, rotation=0, horizontalalignment="right",
 639                verticalalignment="center")
 640            axis.set_xlim(self.xlim)
 641            if name in self.gui_config.pervasive_tiers:
 642                for data_axis in self.data_axes:
 643                    boundary_set = plot_satgrid_tier(
 644                        data_axis, tier, time_offset=stimulus_onset,
 645                        draw_text=False)[0]
 646                    boundaries_by_axis.append(boundary_set)
 647
 648            # Change rows to be individual boundaries instead of axis. This
 649            # makes it possible to create animators for each boundary as
 650            # represented by multiple lines on different axes.
 651            boundaries_by_boundary = list(map(list, zip(*boundaries_by_axis)))
 652
 653            for boundaries, interval in zip(
 654                    boundaries_by_boundary, tier, strict=True):
 655                animator = BoundaryAnimator(
 656                    main_window=self,
 657                    boundaries=boundaries,
 658                    segment=interval,
 659                    epsilon=self.main_config.epsilon,
 660                    time_offset=stimulus_onset)
 661                animator.connect()
 662                self.animators.append(animator)
 663        if self.tier_axes:
 664            self.tier_axes[-1].set_xlabel("Time (s), go-signal at 0 s.")
 665
 666        self.figure.tight_layout()
 667
 668        if self.current.annotations['selected_time'] > -1:
 669            for axes in self.data_axes:
 670                axes.axvline(x=self.current.annotations['selected_time'],
 671                             linestyle=':', color="deepskyblue", lw=1)
 672            self.data_axes[-1].axvline(
 673                x=self.current.annotations['selected_time'],
 674                linestyle=':', color="white", lw=1)
 675            for axes in self.tier_axes:
 676                axes.axvline(x=self.current.annotations['selected_time'],
 677                             linestyle=':', color="deepskyblue", lw=1)

 679    def draw_ultra_frame(self):
 680        """
 681        Display an already interpolated ultrasound frame.
 682        """
 683        if self.current.annotations['selection_index'] == -1:
 684            self.action_export_ultrasound_frame.setEnabled(False)
 685            self.ultra_axes.clear()
 686            image_name = 'AggregateImage mean on RawUltrasound'
 687            if image_name in self.current.statistics:
 688                stat = self.current.statistics[image_name]
 689                image = stat.data
 690                self.ultra_axes.imshow(
 691                    image, interpolation='nearest', cmap='gray',
 692                    extent=(-image.shape[1] / 2 - .5, image.shape[1] / 2 + .5,
 693                            -.5, image.shape[0] + .5))
 694        elif self.current.annotations['selection_index'] >= 0:
 695            self.action_export_ultrasound_frame.setEnabled(True)
 696            self.ultra_axes.clear()
 697            index = self.current.annotations['selection_index']
 698
 699            ultrasound = self.current.modalities['RawUltrasound']
 700            image = ultrasound.interpolated_image(index)
 701
 702            self.ultra_axes.imshow(
 703                image, interpolation='nearest', cmap='gray',
 704                extent=(-image.shape[1] / 2 - .5, image.shape[1] / 2 + .5,
 705                        -.5, image.shape[0] + .5))
 706
 707            if 'Splines' in self.current.modalities:
 708                splines = self.current.modalities['Splines']
 709                index = self.current.annotations['selection_index']
 710                ultra = self.current.modalities['RawUltrasound']
 711                timestamp = ultra.timevector[index]
 712
 713                spline_index = np.argmin(
 714                    np.abs(splines.timevector - timestamp))
 715
 716                # TODO: move this to reading splines/end of loading and make
 717                # the system warn the user when there is a creeping
 718                # discrepancy. also make it an integration test where
 719                # spline_test_token1 gets run and triggers this
 720                # ic(splines.timevector)
 721                # ic(ultra.timevector[:len(splines.timevector)])
 722                # time_diff = splines.timevector - \
 723                #     ultra.timevector[:len(splines.timevector)]
 724                # ic(np.diff(time_diff, n=1))
 725                # ic(np.max(np.abs(np.diff(time_diff, n=1))))
 726
 727                epsilon = max((self.main_config.epsilon, splines.time_precision))
 728                min_difference = abs(
 729                    splines.timevector[spline_index] - timestamp)
 730                # maybe this instead when loading data
 731                # str(number)[::-1].find('.') -> precision
 732
 733                # ic(epsilon, splines.timevector[spline_index] - timestamp)
 734                # ic(splines.timevector[spline_index], timestamp)
 735                if min_difference > epsilon:
 736                    _logger.info("Splines out of synch in %s.",
 737                                 self.current.basename)
 738                    _logger.info("Minimal difference: %f, epsilon: %f",
 739                                 min_difference, epsilon)
 740
 741                spline_config = self.session.metadata.spline_config
 742                if spline_config.data_config:
 743                    limits = spline_config.data_config.ignore_points
 744                    plot_spline(self.ultra_axes,
 745                                splines.cartesian_spline(spline_index),
 746                                limits=limits)
 747                else:
 748                    plot_spline(self.ultra_axes,
 749                                splines.cartesian_spline(spline_index))
 750            else:
 751                _logger.info("No splines")
 752        self.ultra_canvas.draw()

 754    def draw_raw_ultra_frame(self):
 755        """
 756        Interpolate and display a raw ultrasound frame.
 757        """
 758        if self.current.annotations['selection_index'] > -1:
 759            self.action_export_ultrasound_frame.setEnabled(True)
 760            ind = self.current.annotations['selection_index']
 761            array = self.current.modalities['RawUltrasound'].data[ind, :, :]
 762        else:
 763            self.action_export_ultrasound_frame.setEnabled(False)
 764            if self.current.statistics['Aggregate mean on RawUltrasound']:
 765                array = self.current.modalities[
 766                    'Aggregate mean on RawUltrasound'].data
 767            else:
 768                array = self.current.modalities['RawUltrasound'].data[1, :, :]
 769        array = np.transpose(array)
 770        array = np.flip(array, 0).copy()
 771        array = array.astype(np.int8)
 772        self.ultra_axes.imshow(array, interpolation='nearest', cmap='gray')
 773        self.ultra_canvas.draw()

 786    def _update_pd_onset(self):
 787        audio = self.current.modalities['MonoAudio']
 788        if audio.go_signal is None:
 789            stimulus_onset = 0
 790        else:
 791            stimulus_onset = audio.go_signal
 792
 793        if 'PD l1 on RawUltrasound' in self.current.modalities:
 794            pd_metrics = self.current.modalities['PD l1 on RawUltrasound']
 795            ultra_time = pd_metrics.timevector - stimulus_onset
 796            index = self.current.annotations['selection_index']
 797            self.current.annotations['selected_time'] = ultra_time[index]

 799    def next_frame(self):
 800        """
 801        Move the data cursor to the next frame.
 802        """
 803        if 'PD l1 on RawUltrasound' not in self.current.modalities:
 804            return
 805
 806        selection_index = self.current.annotations['selection_index']
 807        pd = self.current.modalities['PD l1 on RawUltrasound']
 808        data_length = pd.data.size
 809        if -1 < selection_index < data_length:
 810            self.current.annotations['selection_index'] += 1
 811            _logger.debug(
 812                "next frame: %d",
 813                (self.current.annotations['selection_index']))
 814            self._update_pd_onset()
 815            self.update()
 816            self.update_ui()

1069    def export_annotations_and_metadata(self) -> None:
1070        """
1071        Export annotations and some other meta data.
1072        """
1073        (filename, _) = QFileDialog.getSaveFileName(
1074            self, 'Save file', directory='.', filter="CSV files (*.csv)")
1075
1076        if not filename:
1077            return
1078
1079        vowels = ['a', 'A', 'e', 'E', 'i', 'I',
1080                  'o', 'O', 'u', '@', "@`", 'OI', 'V']
1081        fieldnames = ['basename', 'date_and_time', 'prompt', 'C1', 'C1_dur',
1082                      'word_dur', 'first_sound',
1083                      'first_sound_type', 'first_sound_dur', 'AAI']
1084        fieldnames.extend(self.default_annotations.keys())
1085        csv.register_dialect('tabseparated', delimiter='\t',
1086                             quoting=csv.QUOTE_NONE)
1087
1088        with closing(open(filename, 'w', encoding='utf-8')) as csvfile:
1089            writer = csv.DictWriter(csvfile, fieldnames, extrasaction='ignore',
1090                                    dialect='tabseparated')
1091
1092            writer.writeheader()
1093            for recording in self.recordings:
1094                annotations = recording.annotations.copy()
1095                annotations['basename'] = recording.basename
1096                annotations['date_and_time'] = (
1097                    recording.metadata.time_of_recording)
1098                annotations['prompt'] = recording.metadata.prompt
1099                annotations['word'] = recording.metadata.prompt.split()[0]
1100
1101                word_dur = -1.0
1102                acoustic_onset = -1.0
1103                if 'word' in recording.textgrid:
1104                    for interval in recording.textgrid['word']:
1105                        # change this to access the phonemeDict and
1106                        # check for included words, then search for
1107                        # phonemes based on the same
1108                        if interval.text == "":
1109                            continue
1110
1111                        # Before 1.0: check if there is a duration to use here.
1112                        # and maybe make this more intelligent by selecting
1113                        # purposefully the last non-empty first and taking the
1114                        # duration?
1115                        word_dur = interval.dur
1116                        stimulus_onset = (
1117                            recording['MonoAudio'].go_signal)
1118                        acoustic_onset = interval.xmin - stimulus_onset
1119                        break
1120                    annotations['word_dur'] = word_dur
1121                else:
1122                    annotations['word_dur'] = -1.0
1123
1124                if acoustic_onset < 0 or annotations['selected_time'] < 0:
1125                    aai = -1.0
1126                else:
1127                    aai = acoustic_onset - annotations['selected_time']
1128                annotations['AAI'] = aai
1129
1130                first_sound_dur = -1.0
1131                first_sound = ""
1132                if 'segment' in recording.textgrid:
1133                    for interval in recording.textgrid['segment']:
1134                        if interval.text and interval.text != 'beep':
1135                            first_sound_dur = interval.dur
1136                            first_sound = interval.text
1137                            break
1138                annotations['first_sound_dur'] = first_sound_dur
1139                annotations['first_sound'] = first_sound
1140                if first_sound in vowels:
1141                    annotations['first_sound_type'] = 'V'
1142                else:
1143                    annotations['first_sound_type'] = 'C'
1144
1145                annotations['C1'] = recording.metadata.prompt[0]
1146                writer.writerow(annotations)
1147            _logger.info(
1148                "Wrote onset data in file %s.", filename)

1168    def onpick(self, event):
1169        """
1170        Callback for handling time selection on events.
1171        """
1172        if not event.xdata:
1173            self.current.annotations['selected_time'] = -1
1174            self.current.annotations['selection_index'] = -1
1175            self.update()
1176            return
1177
1178        subplot = 0
1179        for i, axes in enumerate(self.data_axes):
1180            if axes == event.inaxes:
1181                subplot = i + 1
1182                break
1183
1184        _logger.debug(
1185            "Inside onpick - subplot: %d, x=%f",
1186            subplot, event.xdata)
1187
1188        # if subplot == 1:
1189        #     self.current.annotations['selected_time'] = event.pickx
1190
1191        audio = self.current.modalities['MonoAudio']
1192        if audio.go_signal is None:
1193            stimulus_onset = 0
1194        else:
1195            stimulus_onset = audio.go_signal
1196
1197        timevector = (
1198            self.current.modalities['PD l1 on RawUltrasound'].timevector)
1199        distances = np.abs(timevector - stimulus_onset - event.xdata)
1200        self.current.annotations['selection_index'] = np.argmin(distances)
1201        self.current.annotations['selected_time'] = event.xdata
1202
1203        _logger.debug(
1204            "Inside onpick - subplot: %d, index=%d, x=%f",
1205            subplot,
1206            self.current.annotations['selection_index'],
1207            self.current.annotations['selected_time'])
1208
1209        self.update()

1218    # noinspection PyPep8Naming
1219    def keyPressEvent(self, event):
1220        """
1221        Key press callback.
1222
1223        QtPy is silly and wants the callback to have this specific name.
1224        """
1225        if event.key() == Qt.Key.Key_Shift:
1226            self.shift_is_held = True
1227        if event.key() == Qt.Key.Key_I:
1228            self.gui_config.auto_xlim = False
1229            if self.current.annotations['selection_index'] >= 0:
1230                center = self.current.annotations['selected_time']
1231            else:
1232                center = (self.xlim[0] + self.xlim[1]) / 2.0
1233            length = (self.xlim[1] - self.xlim[0]) * .25
1234            self.xlim = (center - length, center + length)

1236                self.gui_config.xlim = self.xlim
1237            self.update()
1238        elif event.key() == Qt.Key.Key_O:
1239            self.gui_config.auto_xlim = False
1240            center = (self.xlim[0] + self.xlim[1]) / 2.0
1241            length = self.xlim[1] - self.xlim[0]
1242            self.xlim = (center - length, center + length)
1243            if self.gui_config.xlim is not None:
1244                self.gui_config.xlim = self.xlim
1245            self.update()
1246        elif event.key() == Qt.Key.Key_A:
1247            self.gui_config.auto_xlim = True
1248            self.gui_config.xlim = None

Qt_Annotator_Window is a GUI class for annotating PD curves.

The annotator works with PD curves and allows selection of a single points (labelled as pdOnset in the saved file). The GUI also displays the waveform, and if TextGrids are provided, the acoustic segment boundaries.

1069    def export_annotations_and_metadata(self) -> None:

1090                                    dialect='tabseparated')

1104                    for interval in recording.textgrid['word']:
1105                        # change this to access the phonemeDict and

1108                        if interval.text == "":
1109                            continue
1110
1111                        # Before 1.0: check if there is a duration to use here.

1121                else:

1219    def keyPressEvent(self, event):
1220        """
1221        Key press callback.
1222
1223        QtPy is silly and wants the callback to have this specific name.
1224        """
1225        if event.key() == Qt.Key.Key_Shift:
1226            self.shift_is_held = True
1227        if event.key() == Qt.Key.Key_I:
1228            self.gui_config.auto_xlim = False
1229            if self.current.annotations['selection_index'] >= 0:
1230                center = self.current.annotations['selected_time']
1231            else:
1232                center = (self.xlim[0] + self.xlim[1]) / 2.0
1233            length = (self.xlim[1] - self.xlim[0]) * .25
1234            self.xlim = (center - length, center + length)
1235            if self.gui_config.xlim is not None:
1236                self.gui_config.xlim = self.xlim
1237            self.update()
1238        elif event.key() == Qt.Key.Key_O:
1239            self.gui_config.auto_xlim = False
1240            center = (self.xlim[0] + self.xlim[1]) / 2.0
1241            length = self.xlim[1] - self.xlim[0]
1242            self.xlim = (center - length, center + length)
1243            if self.gui_config.xlim is not None:
1244                self.gui_config.xlim = self.xlim
1245            self.update()
1246        elif event.key() == Qt.Key.Key_A:
1247            self.gui_config.auto_xlim = True
1248            self.gui_config.xlim = None
